# Privacy Policy

*Last updated: May 2026*

## 1. Who we are

This website is operated by [Your Name / Company Name], based in [Country], EU. You can contact us at [your contact email].

## 2. What data we collect and why

### 2.1 Server logs (all visitors)

Our servers generate operational logs for the purpose of diagnosing technical issues and ensuring service stability. These logs record only timestamps, HTTP method, URL path, and response codes. IP addresses, user agents, and all other identifying information are explicitly excluded from our logs.

As a result, our server logs contain no personal data and fall outside the scope of GDPR. Logs are automatically discarded when containers are recycled on each deployment.

### 2.2 Account data (registered users only)

If you create an account, we collect the information you provide during registration (such as your email address) and store data associated with your account in our database.

**Legal basis:** Performance of a contract (Article 6(1)(b) GDPR) — your account data is necessary to provide the service you signed up for.

**Retention:** We keep your account data for as long as your account is active. You may request deletion at any time (see Section 5).

### 2.3 Session cookie (registered users only)

If you create an account and log in, we set a session cookie to maintain your login state. This cookie is strictly necessary to provide the authenticated service and is deleted when you close your browser.

If you choose "keep me logged in" at login, a persistent cookie is set instead, so you do not need to log in again on your next visit. This cookie is only set if you actively choose this option.

Anonymous users receive no cookies. No third-party cookies are used on this website.

### 2.4 Local browser storage (anonymous users)

If you use the website without registering, any data you create is stored locally in your browser using IndexedDB. This data **never leaves your device** and is never transmitted to or accessible by us.

This means:
- We cannot see, access, or recover your local data
- Your data will be lost if you clear your browser storage
- This data falls outside the scope of GDPR, as we do not process it

